===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the {{w|oracle bone script}}, an {{Han compound|弓|矢|t1=bow|t2=arrow|ls=ic|nocap=y}} – to shoot a bow. In the {{w|bronze inscriptions}}, a hand ({{zh-l|*又}}) drawing the bowstring was added. Hence, a conservative variant is [[𢎤]].

Later the bow and arrow on the left became {{zh-l|*身}} before or during the {{w|clerical script}} period, and the hand came to be written {{zh-l|*寸}}.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*mV-la(k)|t=bow, arrow}}; cognate with {{cog|bo|མདའ||arrow}}, {{cog|my|မြား||arrow}}, {{cog|grt|bra|t=arrow}} <!-- Lashi mjo³³ ʃɿ⁵⁵ "arrow" = myoo: ?; Achang kaŋ³⁵ m̥ʐua³¹ "arrow"; Shixing lɛ⁵⁵ si³³ "arrow" --> (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Hill, 2013}}).

